==Hindi==
===Adverb===
'''नहीं''' (nahii.n)
# [[no]], [[not]], negative respnse to a yes/no question
#:Example: [[बिलकुल]] नहीं - Of course not, absolutely not.
# [[no]], [[not]], representing negation of statements
#:Example: यहाँ गाजर नहीं हैं - There are no carrots here, or "Here carrots not are" in literal order.

====Usage====
Often used with the polite particle [[जी]] to be more polite in answering those given respect as in जी नहीं.

